				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\frac{{\sigma }_{{}^{{{\mbox{116}}}m}{{\mbox{In}}}}}{{\sigma }_{{}^{{{\mbox{115}}}m}{{\mbox{In}}}}}=\frac{{Y}_{{}^{{{\mbox{116}}}m}{{\mbox{In}}}}}{{Y}_{{}^{{{\mbox{115}}}m}{{\mbox{In}}}}}$$\end{document}. The reaction yield of 116mIn and 115mIn are known from the experiment. Then, the relation equation allows to determine the cross section ratio and therefore the neutron energy where the 116mIn isotopes are produced covered by the resonance range for 115mIn production at σ115mIn=\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
